4:
Listen carefully, Teo. The lionfolk are
cursed to bear the burden of our
ancestors' greatest sin.
6:
This includes us, for as long as we
live.
8:
The Royal Key is proof of our crime. It
is our duty to protect it.
10:
Do you understand? You mustn't
forget this...
31:
I shouldn't have asked for her help.
I'm sorry. She must have hit you
hard.
44:
And I am the only other lionfolk left
in this world.
48:
You're like me? But then why are you
working with the dogfolk?
52:
To secure the Crown of the Beast
King. I require its power.
55:
I'm sure you're familiar with it.
Through the authority of the stars, it
gifted people with intelligence.
59:
If we can steal the crown from that
cowardly Whitetail, the lionfolk will
be the ones to rule the world!
63:
Y-you can't do that... We'd just be
repeating...
67:
The sins of our ancestors? No, Teo.
We owe nothing to them.
70:
What have we even done wrong?
Our only crime was being born into
this world.
73:
Do you think all our pain and
hardship is justified?
76:
Or perhaps the one truly at fault is
this awful, twisted world? You can't
tell me you've never had that
thought once.
84:
You can admit it. I won't judge. I feel
the same, after all.
87:
In fact, I don't think anyone in this
world understands your pain more
than I.
91:
Won't you join me in changing this
rotten world, Teo?
95:
I wonder if I could've played outside
with other kids...
98:
If I'd grown up in that world you
want to create.
103:
...Of course you would have. In my
world, you would have nothing to
fear. We'd be accepted by all.
112:
So you were in pain this whole time
as well...
115:
However, you should know that
crushing the world beneath your
heel won't change a thing.
124:
Sometimes forgetting the past and
running away isn't a bad thing, Little
Cub.
130:
Shut your mouth! What would you
know of our pain?!
133:
I won't let you interfere with my
plans!
143:
Teo, why do you protect her? She's
not one of us.
147: No, she isn't. She's not like you or me.
150:
But even though we're different, she
still chose to help me!
159: Don't be foolish! Open your eyes, Teo!
165:
You're the one that needs a
wake-up call, punk!
173:
No, YOU ran off too early.
...Huh. I guess lionfolk really do exist.
181:
False king! Tyrant! You would stand
in our way?
189: Magnos! What's with all the shouting
192: I won't be stopped here. Not now!
201:
Key of the Crown... Bestow a portion
of your power!
209: What the hell? What'd you do?!
213:
Lowly beasts! Under the name of
your new king, destroy them!
